import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='state', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate across all states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Rate')
    plt.legend(title='States', loc='upper right', labels=data['state'].unique())

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    avg_rate_by_state = data.groupby('state')['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='rate', data=avg_rate_by_state)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average rate for each state?', wrap=True)
    chart.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Average Rate')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
